devdoc.details: Contract handling callbacks for deposit, withdrawal, and order execution/cancellation.

OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

addKey(bytes32,uint8).details: Adds a key to the corresponding array based on the state option (Deposit, Withdrawal, Order).

addWithdrawalData(bytes32,uint256,addres.details: Adds withdrawal data for a specific key.

params._lpAmount: The LP amount to be withdrawn.
params._receiver: The address to receive the LP tokens.
params._withdrawalKey: The key associated with the withdrawal data.

afterDepositCancellation(bytes32,((addre.details: Handles actions after a deposit cancellation.

params.key: The key associated with the deposit.

afterDepositExecution(bytes32,((address,.details: Handles actions after a deposit execution.

params.key: The key associated with the deposit.

afterOrderCancellation(bytes32,((address.details: Handles actions after an order cancellation.

params.key: The key associated with the order.

afterOrderExecution(bytes32,((address,ad.details: Handles actions after an order execution.

params.key: The key associated with the order.

afterOrderFrozen(bytes32,((address,addre.details: Handles actions after an order is frozen.

params.key: The key associated with the order.

afterWithdrawalCancellation(bytes32,((ad.details: Handles actions after a withdrawal cancellation.

params.key: The key associated with the withdrawal.

afterWithdrawalExecution(bytes32,((addre.details: Handles actions after a withdrawal execution.

params.key: The key associated with the withdrawal.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the contract with the vault and GMX plugin addresses.

getKeys(uint8).details: Retrieves an array of keys based on the state option (Deposit, Withdrawal, Order).

returns._0: An array of keys associated with the specified state option.

getLockerStatus().details: Checks whether the contract is locked (i.e., no active deposit, withdrawal, or order).

returns._0: True if the contract is locked, false otherwise.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

refundExecutionFee(bytes32,(((string,add.details: Refunds the execution fee to the GMX plugin.

params.key: The key associated with the execution fee.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setConfig(address,address).details: Updates the vault and GMX plugin addresses in the contract configuration.

params._gmxPlugin: New address of the GMX plugin.

setHandler(address,address,address).details: Updates the deposit, withdrawal, and order handlers in the contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
